1: the head tag cotains meta information about the page. this includes the title,link to CSS files,scripts,
character set,and other data that the browser uses but does not display on the page

2:the body tag contains all the content visible to the user _headings ,paragraphs,images,links,lists,etc.
  everything inside<body> appears on the web page.

3:distinction between <head> and <body>
*the browser correctly renders the page
*CSS/js load properly 
*search engines and browsers interpret your page accurately
